import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the dataset
df = pd.read_csv('dataset.csv')

# Group the data by Device Model and User Behavior Class, and count the number of users in each group
behavior_by_device = df.groupby(['Device Model', 'User Behavior Class']).size().reset_index(name='count')

# Pivot the data to create a matrix of Device Model vs User Behavior Class
pivoted = behavior_by_device.pivot(index='Device Model', columns='User Behavior Class', values='count')

# Create a bar plot of the pivoted data
pivoted.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10, 6))
plt.xlabel('Device Model')
plt.ylabel('Number of Users')
plt.title('User Behavior Class Breakdown by Device Model')
plt.legend(title='User Behavior Class')
plt.show()
